      "content": "In a true, immediate fiscal crisis threatening national solvency, prioritizing debt reduction is the more immediate and mathematically urgent necessity to prevent catastrophic default. A default can trigger a complete economic meltdown, instantly wiping out any social gains. While cutting social spending is morally devastating, failing to manage debt can lead to a complete systemic failure, making debt management the paramount responsibility in that extreme scenario.",
      "source": "target",
